    "abstract": "<jats:title>ABSTRACT</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>\n                  Individuals with acute malaria infection generated high levels of antibodies that cross-react with the SARS-CoV-2 Spike protein. Cross-reactive antibodies specifically recognized the sialic acid moiety on N-linked glycans of the Spike protein and do not neutralize\n                  <jats:italic>in vitro</jats:italic>\n                  SARS-CoV-2. Sero-surveillance is critical for monitoring and projecting disease burden and risk during the pandemic; however, routine use of Spike protein-based assays may overestimate SARS-CoV-2 exposure and population-level immunity in malaria-endemic countries.\n                </jats:p>",
    "DOI": "10.1101/2021.05.10.21256855",
